cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with accelerating the inference process of recurrent neural network transducers (RNN-T) which are commonly used in speech recognition and natural language processing tasks. 

It could also belong to cs.SD (Sound) as speech recognition is a major application of RNN-T. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category as RNN-T is a type of machine learning model. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possibility as the paper deals with improving the efficiency of a machine learning model. 

Finally, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely possibility as the paper deals with optimizing the decoding process of RNN-T, which can be seen as a control problem.
